<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n01019b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01019b">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01019b"> 19(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> pretend to be dead</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;{&hellip;] I remember yet the petty tyrannies I practiced on her and against which she never revolted. When she was going out in full dress to attend gatherings of girls of her own age, I would cling to her gown and beseech her to remain. Then she would turn back, take off her holiday attire and stay with me. One day, in jest, she threatened she would die if I were not a good child, and <mark>pretended to be dead</mark>, in fact, sitting in an armchair. The horror caused me by the feigned immobility of my dear sister is perhaps the strongest impression ever made upon me, whom fate did not permit to witness her last sigh. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font>&rdquo; <small> Michael Monahan, <a name="MMAL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MMAL"><cite title="source">Adventures in Life and Letters</cite></a> (1912) 341-2 [Henriette Renan]</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05104a" href="c05all.htm#c05104a">VI.C.05:104(a)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
